originalText.text: This agency sent my mother to a job where she has to work 8 hours per day in a chocolate factory and gets paid $8.50 per hour. She makes $334 a week and has to pay $60 per week to the driver that the agency assigned to drive employees in a regular size van. They pack 17 people in that van where they have to be for 1 hour and 30 minutes every morning at 7 a.m. and every evening at 5 p.m. My mother has been sent to jobs from this agency before and she’s always had to pay $60 for the van. The worst part is that instead of hiring more drivers and renting or buying more vans, the agency decides to put a bunch of people in a vehicle. Their safety is at risk because most of them cannot even have a seatbelt available to use. But a lot of individuals are in a situation where they don’t have an option but to accept those terms due to their despair. In my opinion, this agency definitely takes advantage of people’s necessities and struggles.

originalText.text: Shady company that posts Ads on craigslist for a specific open position then you receive a call from their main office  scheduling an "interview" for the advertised position only to show up and find out that they are a labor agency and there  are really no open positions and that they just want to sign you up to find a job for you. Come on! It's NYC let's not waste anybody's time!
